reviewText:
This is just Dead Island, but with some GRAPHIC differences:


The bad:

-Excessive bloom, making everything look WAY too bright;
-FORCED Chromatic Aberration (that stays even if you disable it)
-Liquid metal blood (I HOPE it's just a bug that's gonna be fixed eventually;
-No squirting blood from the neck when you chop a zombie's head off anymore;
-Devs went crazy with the post processing effects (sun glare, bloom, haze, motion blur, etc), and you can't even disable most of them;
-Game isn't very well optimized. Runs good, but requires a WAY better PC then the graphics would suggest. Runs worse then Dying Light, in fact.


The good:

+SLIGHTLY better textures;
+Better character models.

Pretty much delivers what advertises:
- a lot better texture work;
- new engine (some graphic effects are borrowed from Dying Light, such as lightning and god rays);
- improved foliage;
- better view distance;
- prettier landscape;
- improved blur effect;
- better depth of field effect;
- optional chromatic aberration;
- improved character and first person models;
- improved particle effects;
and, to make it simple
- a much better overall look.
http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=694952254
And, for the 85% fidelity discount owners of the original franchise get, sounds like a fair deal, IMO.

Haven't seem any change on gameplay, mechanics, weapons or other stuff, but some of the old crazy design choices are still there:
- player character still moves like if they slip over a soapy floor;
- movement is still a bit tight, feeling like you're heavier than you should be;
- zombies still instantly die if you cut off their legs, lol;
- jumping is still weird, specially in third person;
- jumping over obstacles is a bit better now, but still feels sluggish;
- extinguishers are still inflammable, lol;

And some new others:
- some sounds are no longer present, such as the door openning one, chest openning, etc;
- zombies now bleed mercury, LOL.
http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=694952612

And no, the hellish beach ball of death is no longer a concern, you can still kick it, but it will give you just a little bounce and that's it, no more team mate killing with a rubber ball D: .
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YnPUG2vKlls

Apart from this, I'd say it is nice to come back to a game that made me laugh a lot with friends and provided me with tons of fun in the past.

_________________________________

I'll keep updating this review once I find more stuff.
